<file path="docs/provision-pattern/029-industrial-and-financial-protocol-codecs/README.md">
# 029 Industrial And Financial Protocol Codecs

Scenario: an edge payment and telemetry gateway receives a card-present
transaction, builds an ISO8583 authorization payload, emits canonical
Protobuf/MessagePack envelopes, notifies local WebSocket operators, and declares
industrial SOAP/Modbus/OPC-UA integration points.

This example is part of the default compile regression. The live-safe smoke
executes only stateless or loopback-safe paths:

```bash
bash examples-vflow/runtime-smoke/protocol-codecs-live-safe-smoke.sh
```

Coverage:

- ISO8583 encode/decode for payment rails.
- Protobuf and MessagePack encode/decode for internal event contracts.
- WebSocket broadcast on an empty local server as a no-client safe operation.
- SOAP, Modbus, and OPC-UA connector declarations for lab-backed industrial
  integration. These need real simulators/endpoints before docs can claim live
  E2E behavior.
</file>

<file path="docs/provision-pattern/029-industrial-and-financial-protocol-codecs/workflow.yaml">
version: "3.0"
metadata:
  id: industrial-and-financial-protocol-codecs
  name: "Industrial and Financial Protocol Codecs"
  description: |
    Edge gateway workflow for payment authorization and factory telemetry. It
    demonstrates stateless protocol codecs and declares industrial adapter
    calls that require lab endpoints for live E2E execution.
  dialect: vflow
  tags: [example, p1, protocol-codecs, payments, industrial]

spec:
  activities:
    - id: trigger
      activity_type: Trigger
      trigger_config:
        trigger_type: webhook
        route: /examples/protocols/terminal-telemetry
        webhook_config: { path: /examples/protocols/terminal-telemetry, method: POST }
        response_framing: length_prefixed
        end_activity: respond
      output_variable: trigger_payload

    - id: validate_edge_event
      activity_type: Validate
      validate_config:
        input: "$.trigger_payload.body"
        schema:
          required: [terminal_id, transaction_id, amount_cents, machine_node]
          properties:
            terminal_id: { type: string, min_length: 4 }
            transaction_id: { type: string, min_length: 6 }
            amount_cents: { type: integer, minimum: 1 }
            machine_node: { type: string, min_length: 3 }
      output_variable: validated_edge_event

    - id: build_protocol_context
      activity_type: Transform
      input_mappings:
        - target: protocol_context
          source:
            language: v-cel
            source: '{"terminal_id": trigger_payload.body.terminal_id, "transaction_id": trigger_payload.body.transaction_id, "amount_cents": trigger_payload.body.amount_cents, "machine_node": trigger_payload.body.machine_node, "stan": "123456", "iso_amount": "000000" + string(trigger_payload.body.amount_cents), "operator_topic": "examples.protocols.edge"}'
      output_variable: protocol_context

    - id: iso8583_authorization_encode
      activity_type: Connector
      connector_config:
        connector_ref: vastar.iso8583
        operation: encode
      input_mappings:
        - target: mti
          source: { language: literal, source: "0200" }
        - target: fields
          source:
            language: v-cel
            source: '{"3": "000000", "4": protocol_context.iso_amount, "11": protocol_context.stan, "41": protocol_context.terminal_id}'
      output_variable: iso8583_auth

    - id: protobuf_event_encode
      activity_type: Connector
      connector_config:
        connector_ref: vastar.protobuf
        operation: encode
      input_mappings:
        - target: schema
          source:
            language: literal
            source: '{"name":"EdgePaymentEvent","fields":[{"name":"transaction_id","number":1,"type":"string"},{"name":"terminal_id","number":2,"type":"string"},{"name":"amount_cents","number":3,"type":"int64"}]}'
        - target: data
          source:
            language: v-cel
            source: '{"transaction_id": protocol_context.transaction_id, "terminal_id": protocol_context.terminal_id, "amount_cents": protocol_context.amount_cents}'
      output_variable: protobuf_event

    - id: msgpack_event_encode
      activity_type: Connector
      connector_config:
        connector_ref: vastar.msgpack
        operation: encode
      input_mappings:
        - target: value
          source:
            language: v-cel
            source: '{"transaction_id": protocol_context.transaction_id, "terminal_id": protocol_context.terminal_id, "machine_node": protocol_context.machine_node, "rail": "edge-terminal"}'
      output_variable: msgpack_event

    - id: notify_operator_ws
      activity_type: Connector
      connector_config:
        connector_ref: vastar.websocket
        operation: broadcast
      input_mappings:
        - target: topic
          source: { language: spv1, source: "$.protocol_context.operator_topic" }
        - target: message
          source:
            language: v-cel
            source: '{"transaction_id": protocol_context.transaction_id, "terminal_id": protocol_context.terminal_id, "status": "encoded"}'
      output_variable: websocket_notice

    - id: soap_erp_reservation
      activity_type: Connector
      connector_config:
        connector_ref: vastar.soap
        operation: call_action
      input_mappings:
        - target: action
          source: { language: literal, source: "urn:examples:ReserveTerminalBatch" }
        - target: namespace
          source: { language: literal, source: "urn:examples:industrial" }
        - target: body
          source:
            language: v-cel
            source: '"<ReserveTerminalBatch><TransactionId>" + protocol_context.transaction_id + "</TransactionId></ReserveTerminalBatch>"'
      output_variable: soap_result

    - id: modbus_machine_poll
      activity_type: Connector
      connector_config:
        connector_ref: vastar.modbus
        operation: read_registers
      input_mappings:
        - target: address
          source: { language: literal, source: "100" }
        - target: count
          source: { language: literal, source: "4" }
      output_variable: modbus_registers

    - id: opcua_node_read
      activity_type: Connector
      connector_config:
        connector_ref: vastar.opcua
        operation: read_node
      input_mappings:
        - target: node_id
          source: { language: spv1, source: "$.protocol_context.machine_node" }
      output_variable: opcua_node

    - id: accepted_response
      activity_type: Transform
      input_mappings:
        - target: response
          source:
            language: v-cel
            source: '{"status": "encoded", "transaction_id": protocol_context.transaction_id, "terminal_id": protocol_context.terminal_id, "protocols": ["iso8583", "protobuf", "msgpack", "websocket", "soap", "modbus", "opcua"]}'
      output_variable: final_response

    - id: respond
      activity_type: EndTrigger
      end_trigger_config:
        trigger_ref: trigger
        final_response: { language: spv1, source: "$.final_response" }

    - id: end
      activity_type: End

  flows:
    - { id: f01, from: { node: trigger }, to: { node: validate_edge_event } }
    - { id: f02, from: { node: validate_edge_event }, to: { node: build_protocol_context } }
    - { id: f03, from: { node: build_protocol_context }, to: { node: iso8583_authorization_encode } }
    - { id: f04, from: { node: iso8583_authorization_encode }, to: { node: protobuf_event_encode } }
    - { id: f05, from: { node: protobuf_event_encode }, to: { node: msgpack_event_encode } }
    - { id: f06, from: { node: msgpack_event_encode }, to: { node: notify_operator_ws } }
    - { id: f07, from: { node: notify_operator_ws }, to: { node: soap_erp_reservation } }
    - { id: f08, from: { node: soap_erp_reservation }, to: { node: modbus_machine_poll } }
    - { id: f09, from: { node: modbus_machine_poll }, to: { node: opcua_node_read } }
    - { id: f10, from: { node: opcua_node_read }, to: { node: accepted_response } }
    - { id: f11, from: { node: accepted_response }, to: { node: respond } }
    - { id: f12, from: { node: respond }, to: { node: end } }

  variables:
    - { name: trigger_payload, type: object }
    - { name: protocol_context, type: object }
    - { name: final_response, type: object }
</file>

<file path="docs/provision-pattern/030-audit-observability-timeline/README.md">
# 030 Audit Observability Timeline

Scenario: an incident-response workflow emits audit envelopes while the
operator timeline merges runtime state, checkpoints, cancel/retry actions,
HumanTask/EventGateway park state, and audit backends.

The workflow YAML demonstrates the author-facing `metadata.audit_log` and
per-activity `audit_log` declarations. The smoke script validates the concrete
timeline adapter surface that the runtime console uses:

```bash
bash examples-vflow/runtime-smoke/audit-observability-timeline-smoke.sh
```

Adapter coverage:

- JSONL audit-envelope timeline source.
- ClickHouse HTTP source with named tenant/execution parameters.
- Runtime console timeline merge tests.

Operational boundary: the audit dashboard is runtime-local. vflow-cloud may
handoff the user to the runtime console, but it must not proxy this workflow
timeline traffic.
</file>

<file path="docs/provision-pattern/030-audit-observability-timeline/workflow.yaml">
version: "3.0"
metadata:
  id: audit-observability-timeline
  name: "Audit Observability Timeline"
  description: |
    Incident response workflow that demonstrates user-owned audit_log
    channels and operator timeline ingredients. Runtime console merges these
    audit envelopes with statestore events, checkpoints, cancel/retry actions,
    and HumanTask/EventGateway park state.
  dialect: vflow
  tags: [example, p1, audit, observability, timeline]
  audit_log:
    compliance_log:
      enabled: true
      schema_version: "1.0"
      sink_ref: "pack://runtime-observability/compliance"
      subject: "examples.audit.compliance.workflow.v1"
      on: [workflow_started, workflow_succeeded, workflow_failed]
      emit_mode: async_durable
      data_classification: { contains_pii: true, legal_basis: "incident response audit" }
      delivery:
        ack_policy: at_least_once
        retry_policy: { max_attempts: 5, backoff: exponential, initial_delay_ms: 100, max_delay_ms: 3000 }
        dlq_ref: "pack://runtime-observability/audit-dlq"
      retention: "2555d"
    trace_log:
      enabled: true
      schema_version: "1.0"
      sink_ref: "pack://runtime-observability/trace"
      subject: "examples.audit.trace.activity.v1"
      on: [activity_succeeded, activity_failed]
      emit_mode: async
    business_events:
      enabled: true
      schema_version: "1.0"
      sink_ref: "pack://runtime-observability/events"
      subject: "examples.audit.business.workflow.v1"
      on: [workflow_succeeded]
      emit_mode: async

spec:
  durability:
    enabled: true
    default_mode: journal-state

  activities:
    - id: trigger
      activity_type: Trigger
      trigger_config:
        trigger_type: webhook
        route: /examples/audit/incidents
        webhook_config: { path: /examples/audit/incidents, method: POST }
        response_framing: length_prefixed
        end_activity: respond
      output_variable: trigger_payload

    - id: validate_incident
      activity_type: Validate
      audit_log:
        enabled: true
        schema_version: "1.0"
        sink_ref: "pack://runtime-observability/activity-trace"
        subject: "examples.audit.validation.activity.v1"
        on: [activity_succeeded, activity_failed]
        emit_mode: async
      validate_config:
        input: "$.trigger_payload.body"
        schema:
          required: [incident_id, service, severity, summary]
          properties:
            incident_id: { type: string, min_length: 3 }
            service: { type: string, min_length: 2 }
            severity: { type: string, min_length: 2 }
            summary: { type: string, min_length: 5 }
      output_variable: validated_incident

    - id: classify_incident
      activity_type: Transform
      input_mappings:
        - target: incident
          source:
            language: v-cel
            source: '{"incident_id": trigger_payload.body.incident_id, "service": trigger_payload.body.service, "severity": trigger_payload.body.severity, "summary": trigger_payload.body.summary, "major": trigger_payload.body.severity in ["sev1", "sev2"], "timeline_expectation": "statestore events + checkpoints + audit envelopes + park state"}'
      output_variable: incident_context

    - id: escalation_gate
      activity_type: Exclusive

    - id: operator_review
      activity_type: HumanTask
      persistence: ssot
      human_task_config:
        task_type: incident-escalation-review
        assignee: sre_lead
        candidate_groups: [sre, incident_command]
        title: "Major incident escalation review"
        description: "Confirm customer impact, mitigation owner, and communication plan."
        form_ref: incident-escalation-form-v1
        priority: 95
      input_mappings:
        - target: incident
          source: { language: spv1, source: "$.incident_context" }
      output_variable: review_result

    - id: wait_mitigation_signal
      activity_type: EventGateway
      persistence: ssot
      event_gateway_config:
        await: [mitigation-started, mitigation-rejected]
        timeout_ms: 120000

    - id: notify_pager
      activity_type: Connector
      persistence: ssot
      connector_config:
        connector_ref: vastar.http
        operation: post
        timeout_ms: 3000
        retry_policy:
          max_attempts: 2
          base_delay_ms: 250
          max_delay_ms: 1000
          backoff_factor: 2.0
      input_mappings:
        - target: url
          source: { language: literal, source: "http://127.0.0.1:18030/incidents/page" }
        - target: body
          source:
            language: v-cel
            source: '{"incident_id": incident_context.incident_id, "service": incident_context.service, "severity": incident_context.severity}'
      output_variable: pager_result

    - id: accepted_response
      activity_type: Transform
      input_mappings:
        - target: response
          source:
            language: v-cel
            source: '{"status": incident_context.major ? "escalated" : "accepted", "incident_id": incident_context.incident_id, "timeline": incident_context.timeline_expectation}'
      output_variable: final_response

    - id: respond
      activity_type: EndTrigger
      end_trigger_config:
        trigger_ref: trigger
        final_response: { language: spv1, source: "$.final_response" }

    - id: end
      activity_type: End

  flows:
    - { id: f01, from: { node: trigger }, to: { node: validate_incident } }
    - { id: f02, from: { node: validate_incident }, to: { node: classify_incident } }
    - { id: f03, from: { node: classify_incident }, to: { node: escalation_gate } }
    - { id: f04, from: { node: escalation_gate }, to: { node: operator_review }, condition: "incident_context.major", priority: 20 }
    - { id: f05, from: { node: escalation_gate }, to: { node: notify_pager }, type: default, priority: 0 }
    - { id: f06, from: { node: operator_review }, to: { node: wait_mitigation_signal } }
    - { id: f07, from: { node: wait_mitigation_signal }, to: { node: notify_pager }, condition: '_last_output.event == "mitigation-started"', priority: 10 }
    - { id: f08, type: error, from: { node: wait_mitigation_signal }, to: { node: accepted_response } }
    - { id: f09, from: { node: notify_pager }, to: { node: accepted_response } }
    - { id: f10, from: { node: accepted_response }, to: { node: respond } }
    - { id: f11, from: { node: respond }, to: { node: end } }

  variables:
    - { name: trigger_payload, type: object }
    - { name: incident_context, type: object }
    - { name: review_result, type: object }
    - { name: final_response, type: object }
</file>

<file path="docs/provision-pattern/031-versioning-canary-shadow-rollback/README.md">
# 031 Versioning Canary Shadow Rollback

Scenario: a pricing workflow ships as v1, receives a v2 candidate, runs canary
and shadow routing, promotes v2, then rolls back to v1.

The live smoke starts a real `vflow-server`, uploads both YAML versions under a
single workflow id, and calls runtime-local admin APIs:

```bash
bash examples-vflow/runtime-smoke/versioning-canary-shadow-rollback-smoke.sh
```

Expected behavior:

- `workflow-v1.yaml` and `workflow-v2.yaml` upload as versions of
  `versioning-canary-shadow-rollback`.
- Canary split installs on `/examples/versioning/pricing`.
- Shadow mode installs v2 while v1 remains the client response path.
- Promotion activates v2.
- Rollback activates v1 again.
- History, diff, and shadow report endpoints return operator state.
- The HTTP route returns the expected versioned `pricing_engine` response
  across install, promote, and rollback.

This example intentionally documents current-version `Retry` semantics only.
Pinned-version `Replay` is a separate runtime-console action. This example
focuses on rollout controls; add a focused E2E action smoke when proposal docs
need direct UI proof for Replay.
</file>

