<file path="docs/provision-pattern/032-broker-trigger-lab/README.md">
# 032 Broker Trigger Lab

Scenario: an event ingress workflow accepts order events from broker triggers,
normalizes the envelope, and fans the message out to broker families used by
enterprise integrations.

This is a lab/provider example. It is part of the compile regression and is
validated by:

```bash
bash examples-vflow/runtime-smoke/broker-trigger-lab-smoke.sh
```

Current boundary:

- Kafka and MQTT have typed Trigger YAML blocks today.
- RabbitMQ, Pulsar, Pub/Sub, and SQS are represented as Connector activities
  until their runtime trigger adapters are added to the VWFD trigger schema.
- NATS trigger/connector E2E remains covered by `026-nats-event-driven-orders`.

Failure semantics:

- Publish/send connector errors are treated as retryable only when the broker
  failure is connection/timeout/rate-limit class and the workflow preserves the
  `idempotency_key`.
- Side-effecting broker fanout is marked `persistence: ssot`.
- Missing broker endpoints in smoke are `SKIP` by default and fail only under
  strict mode.
</file>

<file path="docs/provision-pattern/032-broker-trigger-lab/workflow-runtime-e2e.yaml">
version: "3.0"
metadata:
  id: broker-trigger-lab-runtime-e2e
  name: "Broker Trigger Lab Runtime E2E"
  description: |
    Runtime E2E fixture for bootstrapped local broker labs. The main
    workflow.yaml keeps the full broker matrix contract, including broker
    trigger declarations and provider connectors. This runtime fixture focuses
    on broker families that the local bootstrap can verify end-to-end:
    Kafka, MQTT, RabbitMQ, and SQS.
  dialect: vflow
  tags: [example, p0, brokers, runtime-e2e]

spec:
  durability:
    enabled: true
    default_mode: journal-state

  activities:
    - id: trigger
      activity_type: Trigger
      trigger_config:
        trigger_type: webhook
        route: /examples/brokers/runtime-e2e
        webhook_config: { path: /examples/brokers/runtime-e2e, method: POST }
        response_framing: length_prefixed
        end_activity: respond
      output_variable: trigger_payload

    - id: validate_event
      activity_type: Validate
      validate_config:
        input: "$.trigger_payload.body"
        schema:
          required: [event_id, order_id, tenant_id, idempotency_key]
          properties:
            event_id: { type: string, min_length: 4 }
            order_id: { type: string, min_length: 3 }
            tenant_id: { type: string, min_length: 3 }
            idempotency_key: { type: string, min_length: 8 }
      output_variable: validated_event

    - id: normalize_event
      activity_type: Transform
      input_mappings:
        - target: broker_context
          source:
            language: v-cel
            source: '{"event_id": trigger_payload.body.event_id, "order_id": trigger_payload.body.order_id, "tenant_id": trigger_payload.body.tenant_id, "idempotency_key": trigger_payload.body.idempotency_key, "payload": {"event_id": trigger_payload.body.event_id, "order_id": trigger_payload.body.order_id, "tenant_id": trigger_payload.body.tenant_id, "source": "runtime-e2e"}}'
      output_variable: broker_context

    - id: publish_kafka
      activity_type: Connector
      persistence: ssot
